   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>PREFACE</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Volume 42 of The Collected Works contains two sections that include various messages given by Watchman Nee in 1936.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Section Four is comprised of messages and fellowship given by Watchman Nee during a conference in Amoy in October 1936.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The messages in the mornings were directed toward the workers and their work.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The fellowship in the afternoon was divided into two groups: 1 free talks and 2 a series of meetings in which Watchman Nee gave his testimony published as Watchman Nee's Testimony in Volume 26 of The Collected Works .</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>"In Christ" was the subject of the evening meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The topics of all the meetings are listed below.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In Section Four, however, the chapters are arranged chronologically in the order that the messages were delivered.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>MORNINGS:</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>October 14: The New Testament Prophet</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>October 15: How to Know God's Will</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>October 16: Knowing Christ and the Power of His Resurrection</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>October 17: The Flesh and the Work of God</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>October 19: Absolute Obedience</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>October 20: The Iniquity of the Sanctuary</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>October 21: Co-workers' Meeting</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>AFTERNOONS:</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>October 15: On Assuming Headship in the Family</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>October 16: Talks 1</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>October 17: Talks 2</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>October 18: Watchman Nee's Testimony 1</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>October 20: Watchman Nee's Testimony 2</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>October 21: Watchman Nee's Testimony 3</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>EVENINGS:</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>October 13: Foot-washing 1</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>October 14: The Foremost Condition for Spiritual Progress</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>October 15: Foot-washing 2</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>October 17: In Christ</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>October 18: In Adam and in Christ</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>October 19: The Subjective Aspect of Being in Christ</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>October 20: The Resurrection of Christ</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>October 21:How to Be in Christ</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Section Five is comprised of messages and fellowship given by Watchman Nee during a conference in Foochow in December 1936.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>The topics of the messages include God's way of accomplishing His purpose and the overcoming life.</S>
